Nigerian internationals Wilfred Ndidi and Kelechi Iheanacho were part of history-making on Saturday evening, May 15, 2021, as their club, Leicester City, beat hard-fighting Chelsea to win the 2021 English FA Cup. A lone goal off a brilliant long-range strike by Youri Tielemans which beat Chelsea goalkeeper Kepa Arrizabalaga in the 63rd minute electrified the sizable crowd that watched the thrilling encounter at the famous Wembley Stadium and ultimately decided the game – handing Leicester City the prized trophy for the first time ever. Striker Iheanacho was substituted later in the second stanza of the game but midfield marshal Ndidi starred till the referee’s final whistle. Goalkeeper and skipper Kasper Schmeichel ensured victory for Leicester with his point-blank saves. A late equaliser by Ben Chiwell was cancelled after VAR adjudged him to have been millimetres offside. •Leicester City match winner Kelechi Iheanacho  Nigerian international Kelechi Iheanacho once more lived up to his billing on Sunday evening when his goal ensured that Leicester City qualified for the English FA Cup final for the first time in 52 years. Iheanacho struck in 55 minutes for what proved to… In "Sports" Nigeria's Kelechi Iheanacho scored twice to help his team dump Manchester United out of the FA Cup. With the 3-1 over Machester United, Leicester City moved into the FA Cup semi-finals for the first time since 1981-82. While Iheanacho scored twice, his teammate, Tielemans got the other goal. The Foxes… In "Sports" ABUJA    -    Nigeria named the following squad on Sunday to compete at the World Cup in Russia this month: Goalkeepers: Daniel Akpeyi (Chippa United), Ikechukwu Ezenwa (Enyimba), Francis Uzoho (Deportivo Coruna) Defenders: Chidozie Awaziem (Nantes), Leon Balogun (Brighton & Hove Albion), Tyronne Ebuehi (ADO Den Haag), Elderson Echiejiole (Cercle… In "Sports"